<li id="cite_note-Kimball1982-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Kimball1982_29-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Kimball1982_29-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball1982" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer W.</a> (1982). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=TA6QAAAAMAAJ"><i>The Teachings of Spencer W. Kimball</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. p.&#160;226. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780884944720" title="Special:BookSources/9780884944720"><bdi>9780884944720</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>Cultural differences pose dangers for marriage. When I said you must teach your people to overcome their prejudices and accept the Indians, I did not mean that you would encourage intermarriage. I mean that they should be brothers, to worship together and to work together and to play together; but we must discourage intermarriage, not because it is sin. I would like to make this very emphatic. A couple has not committed sin if an Indian boy and a white girl are married, or vice versa. It isn't a transgression like the transgressions of which many are guilty. But it is not expedient. Marriage statistics and our general experience convince us that marriage is not easy.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+Spencer+W.+Kimball&amp;rft.pages=226&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.isbn=9780884944720&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DTA6QAAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
