<li id="cite_note-Species-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Species_49-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Species_49-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushman2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Richard_Bushman" title="Richard Bushman">Bushman, Richard Lyman</a> (2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=_izMO9Xdq2UC&amp;pg=PA517"><i>Joseph Smith: Rough Stone Rolling</i></a>. New York: Alfred A. Knopf. p.&#160;517. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-4000-4270-4" title="Special:BookSources/1-4000-4270-4"><bdi>1-4000-4270-4</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>Probably by 'confinement to their own species' he meant no intermarriage.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith%3A+Rough+Stone+Rolling&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pages=517&amp;rft.pub=Alfred+A.+Knopf&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=1-4000-4270-4&amp;rft.aulast=Bushman&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+Lyman&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D_izMO9Xdq2UC%26pg%3DPA517&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
