<li id="cite_note-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith" class="citation book cs1">Smith, Joseph. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.josephsmithpapers.org/paper-summary/journal-december-1842-june-1844-book-3-15-july-1843-29-february-1844/265"><i>Journal, December 1842–June 1844</i></a>. Vol.&#160;3. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. 15 July 1843–29 February 1844 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/The_Joseph_Smith_Papers" title="The Joseph Smith Papers">The Joseph Smith Papers</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Journal%2C+December+1842%E2%80%93June+1844&amp;rft.pages=15+July+1843-29+February+1844&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.josephsmithpapers.org%2Fpaper-summary%2Fjournal-december-1842-june-1844-book-3-15-july-1843-29-february-1844%2F265&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-53"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohnson1992" class="citation book cs1">Johnson, Clark (October 1, 1992). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180629102725/https://rsc.byu.edu/archived/mormon-redress-petitions-documents-1833-1838-missouri-conflict/part-i-published-accounts-1"><i>Mormon Redress Petitions: Documents of the 1833-1838 Missouri Conflict</i></a>. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0884948501" title="Special:BookSources/0884948501"><bdi>0884948501</bdi></a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://rsc.byu.edu/archived/mormon-redress-petitions-documents-1833-1838-missouri-conflict/part-i-published-accounts-1">the original</a> on June 29, 2018<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">June 29,</span> 2018</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/BYU" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU">BYU</a>. <q>We are not prepared to give up our pleasant places and goodly possessions to them [the Mormons]; or to receive into the bosom of our families as fit companions for our wives and daughters, the degraded free negroes and mulattoes, who are now invited [by the Mormons] to settle among us.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Redress+Petitions%3A+Documents+of+the+1833-1838+Missouri+Conflict&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1992-10-01&amp;rft.isbn=0884948501&amp;rft.aulast=Johnson&amp;rft.aufirst=Clark&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Frsc.byu.edu%2Farchived%2Fmormon-redress-petitions-documents-1833-1838-missouri-conflict%2Fpart-i-published-accounts-1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohnson1992" class="citation book cs1">Johnson, Clark (October 1, 1992). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180629102725/https://rsc.byu.edu/archived/mormon-redress-petitions-documents-1833-1838-missouri-conflict/part-i-published-accounts-1"><i>Mormon Redress Petitions: Documents of the 1833-1838 Missouri Conflict</i></a>. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0884948501" title="Special:BookSources/0884948501"><bdi>0884948501</bdi></a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://rsc.byu.edu/archived/mormon-redress-petitions-documents-1833-1838-missouri-conflict/part-i-published-accounts-1">the original</a> on June 29, 2018<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">June 29,</span> 2018</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/BYU" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU">BYU</a>. <q>The statement concerning our invitation to them [black people] to become Mormons, and remove to this state, and settle among us, is a wicked fabrication, as no such thing was ever published in the 'Star', or anywhere else, by our people, nor any thing in the shadow of it; and we challenge the people of Jackson, or any other people, to produce such a publication from us. In fact, one half dozen negroes or mulattoes, never have belonged to our [Mormon] Society, in any part of the world, from its first organization to this day, 1839.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Redress+Petitions%3A+Documents+of+the+1833-1838+Missouri+Conflict&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1992-10-01&amp;rft.isbn=0884948501&amp;rft.aulast=Johnson&amp;rft.aufirst=Clark&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Frsc.byu.edu%2Farchived%2Fmormon-redress-petitions-documents-1833-1838-missouri-conflict%2Fpart-i-published-accounts-1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Cannon-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Cannon_55-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Cannon_55-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Cannon_55-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCannon" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/George_Q._Cannon" title="George Q. Cannon">Cannon, George Q.</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchhistorianspress.org/george-q-cannon"><i>The Journal of George Q. Cannon</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Church_Historian%E2%80%99s_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="Church Historian’s Press">Church Historian’s Press</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Journal+of+George+Q.+Cannon&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.aulast=Cannon&amp;rft.aufirst=George+Q.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchhistorianspress.org%2Fgeorge-q-cannon&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-56"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMarianno2015" class="citation book cs1">Marianno, Scott D. (July 1, 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://digitalcommons.usu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=5480&amp;context=etd"><i>To Belong as Citizens: Race and Marriage in Utah, 1880-1920</i></a>. Logan, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Utah_State_University" title="Utah State University">Utah State University</a>. pp.&#160;57–58<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 26,</span> 2017</span>. <q>In 1897, the First Presidency considered a question related to interracial mixing involving a white husband who married someone 'either black or ... tainted with negro blood.' George Q. Cannon, in determining whether the husband should be ordained to the priesthood, reprised a statement attributed to John Taylor: 'a man who had the priesthood who would marry a woman of the accursed seed' and have the 'law of the Lord ... administered upon him ... would be killed and his offspring for ... the Lord had determined that the seed of Cain should not receive the priesthood in the flesh.' President Cannon feared that administering the priesthood to the offspring of a mixed-race marriage would hazard allowing the 'seed of the murderer [Cain] ... ahead of the seed of Abel who was murdered.'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span></q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=To+Belong+as+Citizens%3A+Race+and+Marriage+in+Utah%2C+1880-1920&amp;rft.place=Logan%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pages=57-58&amp;rft.pub=Utah+State+University&amp;rft.date=2015-07-01&amp;rft.aulast=Marianno&amp;rft.aufirst=Scott+D.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.usu.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D5480%26context%3Detd&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-57"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-57">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation archive">"Council Minutes, 16 Dec. 1897". <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://collections.lib.utah.edu/search?facet_setname_s=uum_gasp">George A. Smith Family Papers</a>, Box: 78, Folder 7. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah" title="University of Utah">University of Utah</a>, <a href="/wiki/J._Willard_Marriott_Library" title="J. Willard Marriott Library">J. Willard Marriott Library</a>.</cite></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-58"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation archive">"18 Aug 1900 Council minutes". <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://archives.lib.byu.edu/repositories/14/resources/1619">Adam S. Bennion papers</a>. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Harold_B._Lee_Library" title="Harold B. Lee Library">Harold B. Lee Library</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>.</cite></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Turner222-59"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Turner222_59-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Turner222_59-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Turner222_59-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTurner2012" class="citation book cs1">Turner, John G. (September 20, 2012). <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/brighamyoungpion0000turn"><i>Brigham Young: Pioneer Prophet</i></a></span> (1st&#160;ed.). Cambridge, MA: <a href="/wiki/Belknap_Press" class="mw-redirect" title="Belknap Press">Belknap Press</a>. p.&#160;222. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0674049673" title="Special:BookSources/978-0674049673"><bdi>978-0674049673</bdi></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 28,</span> 2017</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>If they [the couple and child] were far away from the Gentiles [non-Mormons] they wo[ul]d all have to be killed[.] [W]hen they mingle seed it is death to all. If a black man &amp; white woman come to you &amp; demand baptism can you deny them? [T]he law is their seed shall not be amalg[a]mated. Mulattoes are like mules[,] they can't have the children, but if they will be Eunuchs for the Kingdom of God's Heaven's sake they may have a place in the Temple.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Brigham+Young%3A+Pioneer+Prophet&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+MA&amp;rft.pages=222&amp;rft.edition=1st&amp;rft.pub=Belknap+Press&amp;rft.date=2012-09-20&amp;rft.isbn=978-0674049673&amp;rft.aulast=Turner&amp;rft.aufirst=John+G.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fbrighamyoungpion0000turn&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span> <span class="cs1-visible-error citation-comment"><code class="cs1-code">{{<a href="/wiki/Template:Cite_book" title="Template:Cite book">cite book</a>}}</code>: </span><span class="cs1-visible-error citation-comment">Unknown parameter <code class="cs1-code">&#124;agency=</code> ignored (<a href="/wiki/Help:CS1_errors#parameter_ignored" title="Help:CS1 errors">help</a>)</span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Young1852-60"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Young1852_60-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Young1852_60-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCollier1987" class="citation book cs1">Collier, Fred C. (1987). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=LkRZGQ8oO8IC&amp;pg=PA44"><i>The Teachings of President Brigham Young Vol. 3 1852–1854</i></a>. Collier's Publishing. p.&#160;44. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0934964017" title="Special:BookSources/0934964017"><bdi>0934964017</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>Were the children of God to mingle their seed with the seed of Cain [i.e. Black people] it would not only bring the curse of being deprived of the power of the Priesthood upon them[selves] but they entail it upon their children after them, and they cannot get rid of it. If a man in an unguarded moment should commit such a transgression, if he would walk up and say ["]cut off my head,["] and [one then] kill[ed the] man, woman and child, it would do a great deal towards atoning for the sin. Would this be to curse them? No, it would be a blessing to them—it would do them good, that they might be saved with their brethren. A many would shudder should they hear us talk about killing folk, but it is one of the greatest blessings to some to kill them, although the true principles of it are not understood.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+President+Brigham+Young+Vol.+3+1852%E2%80%931854&amp;rft.pages=44&amp;rft.pub=Collier%27s+Publishing&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=0934964017&amp;rft.aulast=Collier&amp;rft.aufirst=Fred+C.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLkRZGQ8oO8IC%26pg%3DPA44&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Young1865-61"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Young1865_61-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Young1865_61-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFYoung1865" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young" title="Brigham Young">Young, Brigham</a> (1865). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://scriptures.byu.edu/jod/pdf/JoD10/JoD10_0110.pdf">"The Persecutions of the Saints—Their Loyalty to the Constitution—The Mormon Battalion—The Laws of God Relative to the African Race"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>Journal of Discourses</i>. <b>10</b>: 110. <q>Shall I tell you the law of God in regard to the African race? If the white man who belongs to the chosen seed mixes his blood with the seed of Cain, the penalty, under the law of God, is death on the spot. This will always be so.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Discourses&amp;rft.atitle=The+Persecutions+of+the+Saints%E2%80%94Their+Loyalty+to+the+Constitution%E2%80%94The+Mormon+Battalion%E2%80%94The+Laws+of+God+Relative+to+the+African+Race&amp;rft.volume=10&amp;rft.pages=110&amp;rft.date=1865&amp;rft.aulast=Young&amp;rft.aufirst=Brigham&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fscriptures.byu.edu%2Fjod%2Fpdf%2FJoD10%2FJoD10_0110.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-62"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-62">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSchaeffer2009" class="citation news cs1">Schaeffer, Frank (January 12, 2009). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.huffingtonpost.com/frank-schaeffer/perspectives-on-marriage_b_150290.html">"Perspectives on Marriage: Score 1 For Gay America — 0 To The Mormons"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Huffington_Post" class="mw-redirect" title="Huffington Post">Huffington Post</a></i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Huffington+Post&amp;rft.atitle=Perspectives+on+Marriage%3A+Score+1+For+Gay+America+%E2%80%94+0+To+The+Mormons&amp;rft.date=2009-01-12&amp;rft.aulast=Schaeffer&amp;rft.aufirst=Frank&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.com%2Ffrank-schaeffer%2Fperspectives-on-marriage_b_150290.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Image-63"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Image_63-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReynolds1868" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/George_Reynolds_(Mormon)" title="George Reynolds (Mormon)">Reynolds, George</a> (November 1, 1868). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/juvenileinstruct321geor/page/165/mode/1up">"Man and His Varieties: Mixed Races-The Effects of Climate"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Juvenile_Instructor" class="mw-redirect" title="The Juvenile Instructor">The Juvenile Instructor</a></i>. <b>3</b> (21). Salt Lake City: 165 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>Some writers deny the possibility of a mixed race of people existing for any great length of time upon the Earth. They say the race would entirely die out ... There is a great deal of truth in this ... We do not believe in the permanency of a race descended from people so wide apart as the Anglo-Saxon and Negro. In fact we believe it a great sin in the eyes of our Heavenly Father for a white person to marry a black one. And further, it is proof of the mercy of God that that no such race appear [sic] able to continue for many generations.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Juvenile+Instructor&amp;rft.atitle=Man+and+His+Varieties%3A+Mixed+Races-The+Effects+of+Climate&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=21&amp;rft.pages=165&amp;rft.date=1868-11-01&amp;rft.aulast=Reynolds&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fjuvenileinstruct321geor%2Fpage%2F165%2Fmode%2F1up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-64"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-64">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCollier1987" class="citation book cs1">Collier, Fred C. (1987). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=LkRZGQ8oO8IC&amp;pg=PA46"><i>The Teachings of President Brigham Young Vol. 3 1852–1854</i></a>. Collier's Publishing. p.&#160;46. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0934964017" title="Special:BookSources/0934964017"><bdi>0934964017</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>...suppose we ... here declare that it is right to mingle our seed with the black race of Cain, that they shall come in with us and be partakers with us of all the blessings God has given to us. On that very day and hour we should do so, the Priesthood is taken from this Church and Kingdom and God leaves us to our fate. The moment we consent to mingle with the seed of Cain, the Church must go to destruction ....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+President+Brigham+Young+Vol.+3+1852%E2%80%931854&amp;rft.pages=46&amp;rft.pub=Collier%27s+Publishing&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=0934964017&amp;rft.aulast=Collier&amp;rft.aufirst=Fred+C.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLkRZGQ8oO8IC%26pg%3DPA46&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-65"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-65">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTurner2012" class="citation news cs1">Turner, John G. (August 18, 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/19/opinion/sunday/racism-and-the-mormon-church.html">"Why Race Is Still a Problem for Mormons"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Times" title="The New York Times">The New York Times</a></i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Why+Race+Is+Still+a+Problem+for+Mormons&amp;rft.date=2012-08-18&amp;rft.aulast=Turner&amp;rft.aufirst=John+G.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2012%2F08%2F19%2Fopinion%2Fsunday%2Fracism-and-the-mormon-church.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-66"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-66">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCollier1987" class="citation book cs1">Collier, Fred C. (1987). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=LkRZGQ8oO8IC&amp;pg=PA49"><i>The Teachings of President Brigham Young Vol. 3 1852–1854</i></a>. Collier's Publishing. p.&#160;49. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0934964017" title="Special:BookSources/0934964017"><bdi>0934964017</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>if any man mingles his seed with the seed of Cane [i.e. black people] the only way he could get rid of it or have salvation would be to come forward &amp; have his head cut off [and] spill his blood upon the ground. It would also take the life of his [c]hildren.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+President+Brigham+Young+Vol.+3+1852%E2%80%931854&amp;rft.pages=49&amp;rft.pub=Collier%27s+Publishing&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=0934964017&amp;rft.aulast=Collier&amp;rft.aufirst=Fred+C.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLkRZGQ8oO8IC%26pg%3DPA49&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Performance-67"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Performance_67-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Performance_67-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Performance_67-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Performance_67-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPulley_Hudson2015" class="citation journal cs1">Pulley Hudson, Angela (July 2015). "William McCary, Lucy Stanton, and the Performance of Race at Winter Quarters and Beyond". <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Mormon_History" class="mw-redirect" title="Journal of Mormon History">Journal of Mormon History</a></i>. <b>41</b> (3): 97–130. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fjmormhist.41.3.97">10.5406/jmormhist.41.3.97</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.5406/jmormhist.41.3.97">10.5406/jmormhist.41.3.97</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:246563870">246563870</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Mormon+History&amp;rft.atitle=William+McCary%2C+Lucy+Stanton%2C+and+the+Performance+of+Race+at+Winter+Quarters+and+Beyond&amp;rft.volume=41&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=97-130&amp;rft.date=2015-07&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A246563870%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F10.5406%2Fjmormhist.41.3.97%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5406%2Fjmormhist.41.3.97&amp;rft.aulast=Pulley+Hudson&amp;rft.aufirst=Angela&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Preacher-68"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Preacher_68-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Preacher_68-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFStevenson2013" class="citation journal cs1">Stevenson, Russell W. (Spring 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170418060136/http://www.uvu.edu/religiousstudies/docs/2017_msc/russell_stevenson.pdf">"<span class="cs1-kern-left"></span>'A Negro Preacher': The Worlds of Elijah Able"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Mormon_History" class="mw-redirect" title="Journal of Mormon History">Journal of Mormon History</a></i>. <b>39</b> (2): 165–254. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F24243899">10.2307/24243899</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/24243899">24243899</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:254481484">254481484</a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.uvu.edu/religiousstudies/docs/2017_msc/russell_stevenson.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on April 18, 2017 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Mormon+History&amp;rft.atitle=%27A+Negro+Preacher%27%3A+The+Worlds+of+Elijah+Able&amp;rft.ssn=spring&amp;rf