<li id="cite_note-87"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-87">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070115134653/http://emp.byui.edu/SATTERFIELDB/PDF/Quotes/Marriage%20and%20Family%20SWK.pdf">"Teachings Concerning Marriage and Child-Bearing"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://emp.byui.edu/SATTERFIELDB/PDF/Quotes/Marriage%20and%20Family%20SWK.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on January 15, 2007<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 26,</span> 2017</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/BYU-Idaho" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU-Idaho">BYU-Idaho</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Teachings+Concerning+Marriage+and+Child-Bearing&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Femp.byui.edu%2FSATTERFIELDB%2FPDF%2FQuotes%2FMarriage%2520and%2520Family%2520SWK.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-88"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-88">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball1982" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer W.</a> (1982). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=TA6QAAAAMAAJ"><i>The Teachings of Spencer W. Kimball</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. p.&#160;226. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780884944720" title="Special:BookSources/9780884944720"><bdi>9780884944720</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>The interrace marriage problem is not one of inferiority or superiority. ... It is a matter of backgrounds. The difficulties and hazards of marriage are greatly increased where backgrounds are different. ... When one considers marriage, it should be an unselfish thing, but there is not much selflessness when two people of different races plan marriage. They must be thinking selfishly of themselves. They certainly are not considering the problems that will beset each other and that will beset their children. ... We are unanimous, all of the Brethren, in feeling and recommending that Indians marry Indians, and Mexicans marry Mexicans; the Chinese marry Chinese and the Japanese marry Japanese; that the Caucasians marry the Caucasians, and the Arabs marry Arabs.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+Spencer+W.+Kimball&amp;rft.pages=226&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.isbn=9780884944720&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DTA6QAAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-89"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-89">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball" class="citation speech cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://speeches.byu.edu/talks/spencer-w-kimball_marriage-divorce/"><i>Marriage and Divorce</i></a> (Speech). <i>speeches.byu.edu</i>. <a href="/wiki/BYU" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU">BYU</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 28,</span> 2017</span>. <q>We are grateful that this one survey reveals that about 90 percent of the temple marriages hold fast. Because of this, we recommend that people marry those who are of the same racial background generally, and of somewhat the same economic and social and educational background (some of those are not an absolute necessity, but preferred), and above all, the same religious background, without question. In spite of the most favorable matings, the evil one still takes a monumental toll and is the cause for many broken homes and frustrated lives.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Marriage+and+Divorce&amp;rft.pub=BYU&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fspeeches.byu.edu%2Ftalks%2Fspencer-w-kimball_marriage-divorce%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-90"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-90">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRoberts1983" class="citation journal cs1">Roberts, Paul T. (August 1983). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/etd/5078/">"A History of the Development and Objectives of the LDS Church News Section of the Deseret News"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>Theses and Dissertations</i>. [Master's Thesis]. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>, Department of Communications: 7<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">October 29,</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Theses+and+Dissertations&amp;rft.atitle=A+History+of+the+Development+and+Objectives+of+the+LDS+Church+News+Section+of+the+Deseret+News&amp;rft.pages=7&amp;rft.date=1983-08&amp;rft.aulast=Roberts&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+T.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fscholarsarchive.byu.edu%2Fetd%2F5078%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Discouraged-91"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Discouraged_91-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=336&amp;dat=19780617&amp;id=_RxVAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=5866,5012493">"Interracial Marriage Discouraged"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. June 17, 1978<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 27,</span> 2017</span>. <q>For a number of years, President Spencer W. Kimball has counseled young members of the Church to not cross racial lines in dating and marrying.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Deseret+News&amp;rft.atitle=Interracial+Marriage+Discouraged&amp;rft.date=1978-06-17&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.google.com%2Fnewspapers%3Fnid%3D336%26dat%3D19780617%26id%3D_RxVAAAAIBAJ%26pg%3D5866%2C5012493&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-92"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-92">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMillet2003" class="citation news cs1">Millet, Robert L. (June 27, 2003). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://newsroom.churchofjesuschrist.org/article/church-response-to-jon-krakauers-under-the-banner-of-heaven">"Church Response to Jon Krakauer's Under the Banner of Heaven"</a>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Church+Response+to+Jon+Krakauer%27s+Under+the+Banner+of+Heaven&amp;rft.date=2003-06-27&amp;rft.aulast=Millet&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Farticle%2Fchurch-response-to-jon-krakauers-under-the-banner-of-heaven&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-93"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-93">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFletcher_Stack2008" class="citation news cs1"><a href="/wiki/Peggy_Fletcher_Stack" title="Peggy Fletcher Stack">Fletcher Stack, Peggy</a> (June 8, 2008). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://archive.sltrib.com/story.php?ref=/news/ci_9497769">"Mormon and Black: Grappling with a racist past"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Salt_Lake_Tribune" title="The Salt Lake Tribune">The Salt Lake Tribune</a></i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 28,</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Salt+Lake+Tribune&amp;rft.atitle=Mormon+and+Black%3A+Grappling+with+a+racist+past&amp;rft.date=2008-06-08&amp;rft.aulast=Fletcher+Stack&amp;rft.aufirst=Peggy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farchive.sltrib.com%2Fstory.php%3Fref%3D%2Fnews%2Fci_9497769&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Black_Saints-94"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Black_Saints_94-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFEmbry1994" class="citation book cs1">Embry, Jessie L. (1994). <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/blacksaintsinwhi0000embr"><i>Black Saints in a White Church</i></a></span>. <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-56085-044-2" title="Special:BookSources/1-56085-044-2"><bdi>1-56085-044-2</bdi></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 26,</span> 2017</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Black+Saints+in+a+White+Church&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=1-56085-044-2&amp;rft.aulast=Embry&amp;rft.aufirst=Jessie+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fblacksaintsinwhi0000embr&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-95"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-95">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNelson" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Russell_M._Nelson" title="Russell M. Nelson">Nelson, Russell</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/general-conference/1995/04/children-of-the-covenant?lang=eng">"Children of the Covenant"</a>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 28,</span> 2017</span>. <q>The commandment to love our neighbors without discrimination is certain. But it must not be misunderstood. It applies generally. Selection of a marriage partner, on the other hand, involves specific and not general criteria. After all, one person can only be married to one individual. The probabilities of a successful marriage are known to be much greater if both the husband and wife are united in their religion, language, culture, and ethnic background.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Children+of+the+Covenant&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.aulast=Nelson&amp;rft.aufirst=Russell&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fgeneral-conference%2F1995%2F04%2Fchildren-of-the-covenant%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-96"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-96">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRiess2024" class="citation news cs1"><a href="/wiki/Jana_Riess" title="Jana Riess">Riess, Jana</a> (March 8, 2024). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240309020640/https://www.sltrib.com/religion/2024/03/08/jana-riess-who-is-leaving-lds/">"Who is leaving the LDS Church? Eight key survey findings"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Salt_Lake_Tribune" title="The Salt Lake Tribune">The Salt Lake Tribune</a></i>. Salt Lake City, Utah. <a href="/wiki/Religion_News_Service" title="Religion News Service">Religion News Service</a>. Archived from <span class="id-lock-limited" title="Free access subject to limited trial, subscription normally required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.sltrib.com/religion/2024/03/08/jana-riess-who-is-leaving-lds/">the original</a></span> on March 9, 2024 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Salt+Lake+Tribune&amp;rft.atitle=Who+is+leaving+the+LDS+Church%3F+Eight+key+survey+findings&amp;rft.date=2024-03-08&amp;rft.aulast=Riess&amp;rft.aufirst=Jana&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sltrib.com%2Freligion%2F2024%2F03%2F08%2Fjana-riess-who-is-leaving-lds%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInterracial+marriage+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
